snippet.textDisplay: I once did a favor for an old friend of mine. He had asked me if I could go and pick up his moms SUV from a restaurant parking lot. She was takin to the hospital after falling . Anyways it was in the middle if the day and the temperature was at least 110 to 115 . So after I pick up my wife so she can drive my truck back for me we head out. After finding her vehicle I tell my wife that I would meet her at my friend's house  which was about an hour drive away.  Once I opened the door my eyes immediately started to burn, and it felt like I had gotten kicked square in the chest. To make a long story short I had to drive a SUV with the back end(3rd row seat area)  filled with kitty litter  and sh@t and urine. My eyes burned soooo bad,I couldn't breath.  To make matters worse the driver window wouldn't roll down. The only window that worked was the passenger rear window. Tried it for a few miles and it just blew that stuff everywhere. I called my friend and told him to hook up to my trailer and bring it to where I was because I was not moving that vehicle another inch. The things we are willing to do for friends, or should I say the things we will not do for friends. Thinking about giving him your number.  Lol. Keep up the Great work young man.
